Why These Attractors Matter

For a system like GI:HRE, attractors are extremely useful.

They act like macro-level patterns that appear repeatedly in simulations.

Instead of asking:

“What exact civilization will appear?”

You ask:

“Which attractor basin does this environment fall into?”

Example:

Conditions	Likely Attractor
river agriculture + large population	agrarian bureaucracy
island trade hubs	maritime network
open grasslands	nomadic confederation
high energy technology	industrial system

The simulation can then explore variations within that attractor.

